

=Description=

Fabien Bethge:

"a peer-to-peer (P2P) kind of transaction-oriented communities emerged, which origi-nated from simple classifieds but gained many more sophisticated community features as more and more of them went online. Like in normal classifieds in transaction-oriented P2P communities every-one can announce offers or demands on the one hand and everyone can react to that on the other hand.

...

While in the classic classifieds mainly cars, jobs, real estates and partners were announced, the new forms of transaction-oriented P2P communities also embrace the sharing of everyday things like books, household items, assignments, food preparation or community gardening (Latitude & Sharable Magazine, 2010). Also activities like couch surfing and car sharing are organized over these platforms."
(http://p2pfoundation.net/Web_Based_Face-to-Face_Economy)


=Discussion=

Fabien Bethge:

"Transaction-oriented P2P communities promise to have three main potentials for social devel-opment:

1. More open access to people everyday’s activities, projects and resources leads to social integration and attraction of the “creative class” (Florida, 2003) – One trend related to that is called “mass mingling” (Trendwatching.com, 2010): „Constant updates, GPS and mobile online access is now bringing this explosion of dating, net-working, socializing and mingling to the real world domain.“ 

2. Faster innovation for companies (open innovation), customers (collaborative consumption, transumerism) and society

3. More efficient usage of idle resources (private properties, talents, etc.)"
(http://p2pfoundation.net/Web_Based_Face-to-Face_Economy)


